item.title: 6.1.3 jailbreak iphone 4s
item.dc:creator: @Jayden2 Jayden.
item.description:
@Jayden2 wrote:

[quote=“sk8rdude461, post:6, topic:515978”][quote author=KroniKz_ link=topic=634233.msg4284361#msg4284361 date=1366142839]

I can’t find one, is there one yet?

To answer your question shortly. No
The reason:
The iPhone 4S, iPod 5, and some version of the iPad and iPad mini have the A5 chip in them. The A5 cannot be hacked as of this moment. All jailbreaks are done on the A4 currently.

No 6.1.2 has an available jailbreak, for A5 chips.
[/quote]
Well then there isn’t one for 6.1.3, because all the major breakers are working on iOS7.

Edit:
I remember now. Downgrading hasn’t been done on the A5 from what I’ve seen/read.[/quote]

Yes, you’re right. There isn’t one currently.
